# Proposal Template Maintenance

This repo separates template code from client proposal content.

- Treat `app/`, `components/`, `lib/types.ts`, and global styles as the reusable template. Do not change them when the user only asks to add a new client proposal.
- New client proposals should normally be added as `lib/proposals/[client-project-slug].config.ts`.
- Register every new proposal in `lib/proposals/index.ts`.
- Keep proposal content shaped exactly as `ProposalConfig`.
- Preserve Qubo brand casing as `Qubo` in visible text.
- Do not invent prices, timelines, legal claims, or guarantees. If missing, ask or mark as pending for validation.
- Keep routes private-by-link unless the user asks for authentication. Prefer professional, non-guessable slugs for client links.
- After adding or editing a proposal, run lint or at least check TypeScript/linter diagnostics for touched files.

When uncertain, protect the template and only modify proposal data.
